newsitem.title: USA: Nebraska cattle trade at $73-$74, $117-$119 - USDA.
newsitem.headline: Nebraska cattle trade at $73-$74, $117-$119 - USDA.

text.p: Slaughter steers and heifers not well established on a live basis, but undertone lower, particularly after 1200CST/1800GMT.

Demand and seller interest only fair at best, with some buyers reducing bids as day progresses. Sales Confirmed: 14,300 Last Week: 44,200 Last Year: 12,400 Week To Date:19,500 Sm Pd Lst Wk: 54,100 Sm Pd Lst Yr: 17,700
Slaughter Steers: Several pens early in far West Select and Choice 2-3 1250-1375 lbs 73.00, few 74.00. Not tested late.
Slaughter Heifers: Several pens early in far West Select and Choice 2-3 1150 lbs 73.00, few 74.00. Not tested late.
Dressed Basis Delivered. Steers, heifers fully 1.00 lower.
Dressed Basis Steers: Select and Choice 2-3 1200-1325 lbs 116.00 to mostly 117.00, instances to 118.00; some early carrying larger percentage of Choice 119.00. ( weighted average 117.16 )
Dressed Basis Heifers: Select and Choice 2-3 1050-1225 lbs 116.00 to mostly 117.00, instances to 118.00; some early carrying larger percentage of Choice 119.00. ( weighted average 117.39 ).
